Sega, S.A. SONIC (also known as Segasa and Segasa d.b.a. Sonic) is a Spanish coin-operated amusement machines company established by Sega Enterprises-related shareholders in March 1968. By 1972, the company was a pioneer of the import of the video arcade games to Europe, starting with Pong, followed by Space Invaders, Galaxian and Asteroids. They produced pinball machines between 1972 and 1986. First, they imported American pinball machines during the sixties and seventies and later decided to make their own. Their most successful pinball machines were produced under the brand name SONIC and include "American horror"
